Package org.anchoranalysis.feature.session.calculator

Interface FeatureCalculatorMulti<T extends FeatureInput>

Type Parameters:
T - feature input-type
All Known Subinterfaces:
FeatureTableCalculator<T>
All Known Implementing Classes:
FeatureCalculatorCachedMulti, FeatureCalculatorMultiChangeInput, FeatureCalculatorMultiFromSingle, FeatureCalculatorMultiReuse, PairsTableCalculator, SequentialSession, SingleTableCalculator
public interface FeatureCalculatorMulti<T extends FeatureInput>
Calculates one or more features for given params
Author:
Owen Feehan

  • Method Summary

    Modifier and Type Method Description
    ResultsVector calculate​(T input)
    Performs one calculation throwing an exception if something goes wrong
    default ResultsVector calculate​(T input, ErrorReporter errorReporter, boolean suppressErrors)
    Performs one calculation, either calling calculate(T) or calculateSuppressErrors(T, org.anchoranalysis.core.error.reporter.ErrorReporter) depending on a flag
    ResultsVector calculate​(T input, FeatureList<T> featuresSubset)
    Performs one calculation on a sub-set of the feature list throwing an exception if something goes wrong
    ResultsVector calculateSuppressErrors​(T input, ErrorReporter errorReporter)
    Performs one calculation recording the error to an ErrorReporter if anything goes wrong, but throwing no exception
    int sizeFeatures()
    The number of features that is calculated on each call to calc(), and therefore the size of the ResultsVector returned
